<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="554" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,962,1166]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,962,987]" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is also characterized by large semi-spherical eyes and simple thin legs; other characters are strongly flabellate antennae from 6th to 10th segment, entirely black colouration without metallic luster, dark antennae with 1–2 antennomeres monochrome, and 3–5 at bases yellow; anterior legs dark, intermediate from tibiae to tarsi yellow, posterior ones black; size 
<quantity box="[712,854,1070,1095]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.65" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="2.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" unit="mm" value="2.65" valueMax="2.8" valueMin="2.5">2,5–2,8 mm</quantity>
. As in the case of 
<emphasis box="[1079,1106,1071,1094]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">O.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Wittmer" authorityName="Wittmer" box="[1117,1347,1070,1095]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Dromanthomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ranuensis">
<emphasis box="[1117,1226,1071,1094]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">ranuensis</emphasis>
(Wittmer)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[1409,1436,1071,1094]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">O.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Pic" authorityName="Pic" box="[151,353,1106,1131]" class="Insecta" family="Melyridae" genus="Dromanthomorphus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="saigonensis">
<emphasis box="[151,282,1107,1130]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">saigonensis</emphasis>
(Pic)
</taxonomicName>
, the most similar in external appearance, this species should be attributed to the genus 
<emphasis box="[151,332,1142,1166]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="554">Oculapalochrus</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
